In C++, Python, and Java, deque (double-ended queue) implementations are available through different standard libraries

- C++:
Library:  (part of the C++ Standard Template Library - STL)  

Implementation: The C++ STL provides the std::deque container, which is a dynamic array that supports

constant time insertion and removal of elements at both ends. It is implemented as a sequence of 

fixed-size arrays.

```cpp
